{
  "items": [
    {
      "prompt": "You are analyzing sales data where a 'store_sales' table links to an 'customers' table via store_id.\n\nComplete the query below using only INNER JOIN logic, then convert it to LEFT JOIN by:\n1. Removing all filtering on customer columns from WHERE.\n2. Keeping ONLY conditions that MUST match (e.g., active stores).\n3. Ensuring unmatched customers remain in the result set but have NULLs for sales fields.",
      "answer": "\nSELECT \ns.c.*, ss.total\nFROM store_sales ss\nLEFT JOIN customers c ON ss.store_id = c.id AND c.active;\n-- Key: Remove WHERE filters on c.*; keep only active check if strictly required logic, otherwise remove all customer-side conditions from WHERE clause.",
      "rubric": "- Learner correctly removes non-essential filtering from the RIGHT side of the LEFT JOIN.\n- Left join syntax (no outer applied to right table) is used instead of inner filters.",
      "skill": "apply"
    },
    {
      "prompt": "Write SQL that finds customers who visited multiple stores in 2023 but have NO associated 'high_value' transactions.\n\nHint: Start with LEFT JOIN from the customer list to their specific high-value transaction records.",
      "answer": "\nSELECT DISTINCT c.id, c.name\nFROM customers c\nLEFT JOIN (id, store_id) as high_val ON ...\nWHERE cv.store_count > 1 AND cv.total = NULL;\n-- Logic: Join once per visit type; filter where count exists and transaction total is null.",
      "rubric": "- Query uses LEFT JOIN to capture unmatched rows with NULLs for the right table.\n- Filtering logic correctly isolates groups without high-value transactions (where field IS NULL).",
      "skill": "produce"
    },
    {
      "prompt": "Identify three common mistakes when converting an INNER JOIN query to a LEFT JOIN. Provide one code fix for each.",
      "answer": "\n1. Mistake: Keeping WHERE clause on joined table (c.active = 0)\n   Fix: Move condition before the ON or remove from where.\n2. Mistake: Using SELECT * which hides columns\n   Fix: Specify only needed non-null fields to avoid NULL confusion.",
      "rubric": "- Learner identifies at least one WHERE clause filter on joined table as a collapse risk.\n- Provides code-level fix demonstrating removal of right-table filtering or proper selection.",
      "skill": "produce"
    }
  ],
  "note": null,
